Setup framework for application
=================================

Install Java JDK --  sudo apt-get install openjdk-7-jdk -y 
Install sbt: http://www.scala-sbt.org/release/docs/Getting-Started/Setup.html
Download and unzip play framework: http://www.playframework.com/download
Add play framework to PATH (export PATH:$PATH:/home/user/play-2.1.2)


	Debian:

	cd ~/
	sudo apt-get install openjdk-7-jdk -y
	wget http://scalasbt.artifactoryonline.com/scalasbt/sbt-native-packages/org/scala-sbt/sbt//0.12.4/sbt.deb
	sudo dpkg -i sbt.deb
	wget http://downloads.typesafe.com/play/2.1.2/play-2.1.2.zip
	unzip play-2.1.2.zip
	echo 'export PATH=$PATH:'$HOME'/play-2.1.2' >> ~/.bashrc
	source ~/.bashrc
	#Cleanup
	rm play-2.1.2.zip
	rm sbt.deb


Running application:
> cd BeamstreamPlay
> sbt play run

Running application with development.conf:
>  sbt play -Dconfig.file=conf/development.conf run
